The paper proposes a novel framework for motion correction in multishot MRI using generative networks and conjugate gradient SENSE reconstruction. This involves using deep learning techniques such as generative adversarial networks (GANs) and sensitivity encoding (SENSE). Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV) followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves medical imaging (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) which are also likely categories.
